        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 6:17PM CDT by NWS New Orleans LA</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roseland, or near Amite, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greensburg, Amite, Amite City, Roseland, Montpelier, and Tangipahoa.

This includes Interstate 55 in Louisiana between mile markers 43 and
59.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
